The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) for optimizing building energy control and power system planning. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) as RL is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also involves the use of multi-agent systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The optimization of energy usage in buildings falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE), and the use of game theory in demand-side management falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
